                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 5072/43.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Bulgarian Minister for Foreign Affairs</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1909-06-02">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 2, 1909</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Excellency</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the
                    receipt of your note of the 2/15 ultimo, by which you are so good as to inform
                    me that the powers signatories to the treaty of Berlin have recognized Bulgaria
                    as independent and its sovereign as King of the Bulgars.</p>
                <p>In thanking your excellency for the courtesy of your note I gladly avail myself
                    of the opportunity to renew to you the felicitations of the United States and
                    the assurances of the cordial friendship of this Government and people, which
                    the diplomatic representative of the United States accredited to your Government
                    was instructed by the President to convey to His Majesty the King.</p>
                <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
